profile_positions.description:
Responsibilities:

Budget development:
•	Preparation of the Tribunal’s annual budget, special grants, and project-based trust funds; 
•	Developing standard cost tables, spreadsheets for collecting and collating numerical data, and assisting with writing budget narratives; 
•	Reviewing budget submissions for compliance with set guidelines and parameters; 
•	Analysis and reporting of areas of budget growth in relation to trial and investigation activities. 

Budget control and reporting:
•	Reviewing of obligating documents for verification for fund availability, compliance to the financial rules and regulations, and compliance to the functional plan of the Tribunal.
•	Assisting with the preparation of the periodic performance reports, clarification/explanation of abnormal expenditures and deviation to the budget, and revision of year-end expenditure forecast;
•	Entering account allotments and fund realignments/redeployments in the Mercury procurement system;
•	Monthly reconciliation between the Procurement (Mercury) and Finance (SUN) systems to identify and resolve discrepancies for budget holders; 
•	Reporting on fund availability and areas of concern;
•	Review of management reports.

Other: 
•	Assisting with the annual audit, and audit of trust funds and special grants;
•	Maintaining the Tribunal’s Staffing Table;
•	Reviewing travel authorizations, and verifying mission expense claims;
•	Controlling and reporting on extra-budgetary funds, trust funds, and government grants;
•	Developing all budget reports and checking report integrity;
•	Providing training and guidance to staff for all budget-related matters.

Responsibilities:
•	Assisted in the preparation of documents  including press and newspaper advertisements
•	Provided day-to-day support and assistance to them. Operations Manager to help keep business running smoothly.
•	Monitored pricing of services in the Enterprise.
•	Answered incoming calls and respond appropriately to all inquiries as well as direct incoming calls when necessary.
•	Notified Management of potential customer service issues in a timely manner.
•	Conducted market research 
•	Computerization of documents.
•	Customer Care.
•	Processing daily bank statements;
•	Account reconciliation;
•	Invoicing customers through SAP Fi/Co;
•	Liaising with the credit and collections unit on late and outstanding payments;
•	Reporting on monthly billing accuracy and timeliness;
•	Assisting with the month and year-end close.
